This paper is primarily focused on regularization techniques for neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these techniques in image classification tasks (cs.CV) and mentions the winning entry to ImageNet 2012. The paper also discusses the mathematical interpretation of neural networks as universal function approximators, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new model for regularization, which involves factorizing weight matrices, which could potentially fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS) or neural networks (cs.NE).
